# Simplified Academic Reader Implementation

The library reader has been streamlined to provide a clean, distraction-free scholarly experience by removing complex sidebars and additional modules.

## Key Changes
- **Removed Sidebars**: Both the left (TOC/Study Tools) and right (High Yield/Related Modules) sidebars have been removed to focus entirely on the document content.
- **Removed Table of Contents**: Navigation is now sequential, reflecting a "traditional book" focus.
- **Removed Study Tools**: Quick Reference and Highlights panels have been removed to reduce UI clutter.
- **Removed Related Modules**: The "More to Read" and "Related Modules" sections have been stripped out.
- **Focused Layout**: The content area is now centered and optimized for long-form reading.

